# Changelog

## [unreleased]

### Removed

- **Remove overlay functionality and related tests**
  - Deleted overlay.go file and removed overlay-related code from tui.go
  - Removed associated test case in tui_concurrency_test.go
  - Overlay feature is no longer needed in the current architecture
  - Note: Overlay functionality will be re-implemented in a future version with improved architecture

## [V0.1.1]

### Fixed

- **Critical: Fixed "Rendered line exceeds terminal width" panic**
  - Root cause: Ambiguous-width Unicode characters (arrows ↑↓←→, box drawing characters ─│┌┐, etc.) were incorrectly calculated as width 2 instead of width 1, causing severe width calculation mismatches
  - Configured `go-runewidth` library with `EastAsianWidth = false` to match modern terminal rendering behavior
  - These characters are now correctly treated as width 1, matching how most terminals actually render them

- **Fixed Unicode character width calculation in text slicing**
  - `SliceWithWidth()` now uses grapheme segmentation with `GraphemeWidth()` instead of treating every character as width 1
  - `ExtractSegments()` now properly handles wide characters (Chinese, Japanese, Korean, emoji, etc.)
  - Ensures accurate text truncation and slicing for all Unicode characters

- **Fixed Editor component width calculation inconsistencies**
  - Removed custom `runeWidth()` function that had inaccurate Unicode range checks
  - Now uses standardized `fasttui.GraphemeWidth()` throughout the codebase
  - Added `fillWithHorizontal()` helper function to correctly fill borders with wide characters
  - Fixed `renderBorder()` to properly calculate repeat count for box drawing characters
  - Added safety checks to ensure rendered lines never exceed terminal width

- **Fixed Footer component to use standard library functions**
  - Replaced custom width calculation functions with `fasttui.VisibleWidth()`
  - Now uses `fasttui.TruncateToWidth()` and `fasttui.SliceByColumn()` for proper Unicode handling
  - Added final width validation to prevent overflow

### Changed

- **Standardized character width calculation across all components**
  - All components now use the same `runewidthCondition` configuration
  - Consistent handling of ambiguous-width characters throughout the library
  - Improved compatibility with various terminal emulators

### Technical Details

- Added `runewidthCondition` global variable in `text_segment.go` with `EastAsianWidth = false`
- Updated `GraphemeWidth()` to use custom runewidth condition
- Added multiple safety checks in rendering pipeline to prevent width overflow
- All existing tests continue to pass with the new width calculation logic

### Impact

- Fixes crashes when using arrows, box drawing characters, or other ambiguous-width Unicode characters
- Improves display accuracy for mixed ASCII and Unicode content
- Better terminal compatibility across different platforms and locales
- Resolves issues where horizontal borders were not displaying completely
